text:
These videos all have endings that will keep
you guessing, and as you are watching, just
remember . . . not all surprises end well.

An officer pulls over a vehicle for running
a red light. He and the driver are having

a discussion about what to do next when it
looks like a third vehicle is trying to get
the officer’s attention off in the distance.

The officer probably guesses he is being flagged
down by someone with an emergency to report,

which happens from time to time during traffic
stops, but that’s not how this video ends
at all.

The headlights continue to grow brighter and
soon the officer realizes this driver has

no intentions of slowing down. He steps around
the back of the car moments before getting

flattened.
I don’t know if the person driving was just

completely not paying attention, but this
is a major violation that could easily land

them behind bars.
The police officer lets the first person go

and ducks into his squad car to pursue the
other car. I’m sure this is definitely not

how they were expecting the traffic stop to
end.

This Oklahoma weather report has an interruption
and an ending that you will never guess.

An earthquake rips through the building and
threatens to collapse its very foundations.

I think most people would run for cover, but
her reaction will probably surprise you more
than the actual event.

Rather than evacuate, she and the rest of
the crew bravely finish up the weather report

despite getting rocked by an earthquake over
4.0 on the Richter Scale. Let me know if you

would have put your job first and done the
same or if you would have been out of there
immediately.

A news reporter is getting ready to go live
when an elderly local wanders into his frame.

The two politely exchange hellos and the reporter
thinks nothing of it until he squints off

in the distance, thinking he recognizes the
person from somewhere.

As it turns out, the man who just passed them
by was the exact same person who they were

seconds away from doing a missing report on.
He has memory problems and had wandered away
yesterday.

Looking at him you wouldn’t be able to tell
anything is wrong with his memory, but his

shoes are wet and he has been wandering in
the wilderness overnight. Fortunately he somehow

found his way back to the road and they were
able to get him before he became too exhausted
and lost.

When this man went after a string of banks
along the Cincinnati Tri-State area, police

were flooded with anonymous calls from people
who claimed to know who it was.

When they went to his mother’s house to
take him into custody, she was extremely distraught

and said she had watched the news and already
knew why they were there. The two pictures

look almost identical and the sunglasses did
little to hide his true identity.

It seems like an open and shut case, but you’ll
never guess the ending. After some more investigating,

they found out the real crook was this man
named Conrad Zerdiak , who had bought a lifelike

mask for a thousand dollars and used it during
his spree.

The mask just so happened to look exactly
like the suspect in question. If Conrad’s

girlfriend hadn’t of turned him in, they
may very well have gotten the wrong guy.

I wonder how many other times a realistic
mask was used to commit a wrongdoing, and

how many other innocent people may be put
behind bars under similar circumstances. After

all, saying that somebody was wearing a mask
that looked just like you is a pretty unbelievable
alibi.

A Russian police officer pulls a car over
at a security checkpoint for questioning,

but he barely has a chance to say anything
before he finds himself jumping in the vehicle

to save his life, and you’ll never guess
from what.

About twenty vicious wolves emerge from the
frosty forest and run in unison down the M23

Highway. I can’t tell if this is computer
generated effects or an unedited CCTV video,

but if this really happened, then the police
officer gets into the car just three seconds

before a large wolf trots by where he just
was standing. He doesn’t even get the door

shut in time and the animal could have jumped
in if it really wanted to.

The wolves must have recently feasted because
they do seem rather unconcerned with him,

but I have little doubt that one of them would
have taken him down just for sport if he had
stood in their way for much longer.

This Birmingham, Alabama restaurant seems
to be rapidly falling apart with surprised

customers still inside. Chunks of ceiling
lay strewn on the ground as more infrastructure
cracks and breaks overhead.

It looks like the ceiling itself is about
to crumble, and it eventually does less than

a minute later, but you’ll never guess the
reason why.
A

stranger busts through the ceiling and lands
on their feet, covered in fiberglass insulation.

Fortunately this happened over an empty table
and not the counter area, where somebody could

have easily gotten harmed. They try to act
like nothing is wrong as they walk to the

exit and drive away.
Later the man is apprehended after a short

chase by police. Investigators think he was
trying to take money from the back office

but accidentally fell through the main dining
room instead. Whatever his reasoning was,

I’m sure the customers never guess their
meal would be ended early by his grand escape.

Two golfers in Florida decide to have some
fun with an alligator near the edge of an

embankment. They tap a golf ball in its direction
just to see how it reacts. Try to translate

what one of them says at the end if you can,
too.

The gator eyes the golf ball and makes a quick
decision. Judging by their surprised reactions,

it’s definitely not the ending they were
expecting.

Notice how the gator seems to hold eye contact
with the person recording. I know these reptiles

have very limited intelligence, but it’s
almost as if the gator knows it has the last

laugh as it slips into the water without breaking
its stare.

A YouTuber named AloneInTheDark takes a two-hour
tour of a haunted hospital that has been out

of commission for a long time. He repeatedly
hears noises and gets signs that he is not

alone, like here for example, when you can
see a light appear out of nowhere in response
to his voice.

At one point on an upper floor he finds a
long streak of dried red liquid running down

the wall from a nearby ceiling vent. It almost
looks like somebody was grabbed from above

by something terribly strong and pulled up
into the ventilation duct where they met a
horrible fate.

Something else strange about this video is
how all of the cabinet doors that he passes

by seem to be flung open. Cabinets opening
by themselves is a classic sign of a haunting,
so take that for what you will.

When he is finally ready to leave, the paranormal
events really pick up in ways you’ll never
guess.

First he hears an ambulance pull up to the
defunct hospital, and then he sees shimmering

lights on the ground. It could just be broken
glass reflecting in the beam of his flashlight,

but then again, it could be a paranormal energy
signature. Either way, the timing of the ambulance

siren is too much of a coincidence for me
to believe this was anything normal.

A European factory worker takes a thin rod
and coaxes molten metal down a chute. Once

he has a steady stream going, he takes off
his protective gear and you’ll never guess
how the video ends.

With no glove and not even so much as a a
jacket to protect his bare arms, the fearless

factory worker swats at the lavalike substance
with just his hand. Watch how the splattered

molten metal scorches a nearby pipe and dries
into thickened black clumps and you can tell
this is definitely real, no editing.

He does this no less than six times and holds
his hand out to show only some blackened fingertips

and nothing more. I have no idea how this
is humanly possible or, more importantly,

how he was even able to discover this bizarre
and rare talent, let alone put it to use at
random.

Before we get to number 1, my name is Chills
and I hope you’re enjoying my narration.

If you’re curious about what I look like
in real life, then go to my instagram, @dylan_is_chillin_yt

and tap that follow button to find out. My
music video for WHO AM I NOW? has been uploaded,

but do not watch it, please please please
don’t. It's a proven fact that generosity

makes you a happier person, so if you're generous
enough to hit that subscribe button and the

bell beside it then thank you. This way you'll
be notified of the new videos I upload every
Thursday and Saturday.

Three masked men attempt a daring heist in
Sydney, Australia at the Miller Shopping Center.

They are in the middle of taking jewels when
literally everyone in the store decides to

their not going to take this. And soon the
men find themselves running for their lives.

Customers and staff join together and chase
the men out of the mall. Not even the fact

one of the masked men is holding a sledgehammer
is enough to hold back the angry vigilante
mob.

The three masked men flee into a red van and
speed away with the mob close behind.

With so many similar instances caught on video,
it’s quite a surprise to see everyone join
in to chase off the robbers for once.
